    <note type="dates"><date>1834–78</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Swiss physician, naturalist, and coffee planter. Studied medicine at the University of Basel and elsewhere; practised in Basel until 1858. Resided in Guatemala, where he owned a coffee plantation, 1858–78. Collected primarily botanical specimens.</p></note>
